The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, July 21, 2004 				 Tribute to a master
																								In remembrance of renowned Russian painter Ilya Efimovich Repin on his 160th birth anniversary, In Celebration of Life, Imaginations fifth group exhibition of paintings, showcases the works of four city artists. Repin, one of the most prominent figures of 19th century Russia, was greatly appreciated for painting his subjects in their basic elements. His famous portraits and dramatic depiction of Russian history made Repin a household name in his country. In Celebration of Life features the paintings of Arindam Bose, Prasanta Acharjee (whose My City appears above), Sudipta Sur and Barindam Bose.																								Event: An Exhibition of painting																								When: Till July 23: 4pm - 7pm																								Where: Gorky Sadan
